			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				A piece of advice: you should bind yourself just<BR>
inside the zone in which you are fighting.  If<BR>
things go really bad, you can gate out and run<BR>
through the zone.  If you just want to get a<BR>
good lead on the mob to summon another pet or<BR>
whatever, you can gate and prepare.  If you die,<BR>
you don't have to wait through a zone to retrieve<BR>
your corpse.<BR>
<BR>
Also, I can think of no cirumstance in which it<BR>
would be a good idea to bind right before you die.<BR>
Remember, if you had enough time and mana to<BR>
bind, you had enought time and mana to gate.<BR>
Which is better, to regen right where your body<BR>
is, or to not die at all? ;-)  Actually, I just<BR>
thought of a circumstance in which it might make<BR>
sense - if you are dying due to a DOT.  Still,<BR>
if you follow my advice above you don't lose much<BR>
time and you don't have to blow a spell slot or<BR>
re-mem for bind.  Just don't forget to hit your<BR>
/loc hotkey when you see that you may be about to<BR>
die!  I advise doing it while recovering from a<BR>
spell.<BR>
<BR>
Hope that helps someone,<BR>
Tobas of Qeynos
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
